<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3947.1.5>
    bibo:endPage "98" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "85" ;
    bibo:volume "3947" ;
    dc:creator "Srinivasulu, Chelmala; Kumar, Gandla Chethan; Srinivasulu, Bhargavi" ;
    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Cnemaspis (Sauria: Gekkonidae) from Northern Karnataka, India" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288352>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288353>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288354>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288355> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288352>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. A – C) Dorsal, lateral and ventral view of the head, D – E) Dorsal and ventral view of the mid-body, F – G) Ventral view of right manus and line drawing showing arrangement of lamellae, H – I) Ventral view of right pes and line drawing showing arrangement of lamellae, and J – K) Pericloacal region showing 2 precloacal pores, 2 femoral pores on right and left thighs, and line drawing showing their location on Cnemaspis adii sp. nov. holotype, NHM. OU. REP. CN. 2 – 2013." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/288352/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288353>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Photographs of Cnemaspis adii sp. nov. in life. A) Adult colouration, dark phase (holotype NHM. OU. REP. CN. 2 – 2013, adult male), B) Adult colouration, light phase (paratype NHM. OU. REP. CN. 1 – 2013, adult female), C) Adult colouration (Not collected)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/288353/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288354>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Map depicting the location of the type locality of Cnemaspis adii sp. nov. in Bellary District, Karnataka, India." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/288354/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.288355>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Type locality of Cnemaspis adii sp. nov. in Hampi, Bellary District, Karnataka, India. A) Temple behind Elephant Stables from where the holotype (NHM. OU. REP. CN. 2 – 2013) and the paratype (NHM. OU. REP. CN. 1 – 2013) were collected, B) Krishna temple from where the subadult paratype (NHM. OU. REP. CN. 3 – 2013) was collected." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/288355/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

